cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this benchmark or its crosswalk, please cite it."
title: "mcp-defense-bench: A Layer-Aware, Framework-Mapped Benchmark for Model Context Protocol Security Proxies"
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Gowthaman
    family-names: Arumugam
    email: agowthaman90@gmail.com
    affiliation: "Independent Researcher"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Gowthaman90/mcp-defense-bench"
url: "https://github.com/Gowthaman90/mcp-defense-bench"
abstract: >-
  A vendor-neutral benchmark measuring how much of the Model Context Protocol
  (MCP) attack surface a defensive proxy actually covers, crosswalked to the
  NIST AI RMF, the NSA MCP Security guidance, and the OWASP Top 10 for LLM and
  Agentic Applications. Includes a 24-vector threat-control crosswalk, a matched
  malicious/benign test corpus, tool adapters, a runner and scorer, and an
  accompanying whitepaper. The strongest of three evaluated open-source proxies
  reaches 63% weighted coverage (15.0 of 24 vectors) at zero false positives.
license: Apache-2.0
